                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi John, I've tried to clarify what I meant in my previous comment."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "John Wang",
                        "email": "wangzhiqiang02@ieisystem.com",
                        "username": "wangzqbj"
                    },
                    "message": "Previously I thought you didn't recommend NOLINTBEGIN/NOLINTEND because the scope of inclusion was too large, but using the NOLINTNEXTLINE directive directly introduces comments within the function arguments, which looks a bit untidy (in my opinion), so I had adjusted it to NOLINTBEGIN/NOLINTEND"
                },
                {
                    "file": "ringbuffer.c",
                    "line": 101,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@codeconstruct.com.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "The change I was suggesting was to stop using `NOLINTBEGIN()`/`NOLINTEND()` and switch to `NOLINTNEXTLINE()`, which reduces the noise:\n\n```\nmemmove(&rb->consumers[i], &rb->consumers[i + 1],\n        /* NOLINTNEXTLINE(bugprone-sizeof-expression) */\n        sizeof(*rb->consumers) * (rb->n_consumers - i));\n```"
                },
                {
                    "file": "ringbuffer.c",
                    "line": 101,
                    "reviewer": {
